          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">In a joint response=
, Skeel and Lipson conceded they might not have been fully informed about <=
i>everything</i> that transpired. For instance, they note that SDNY may alr=
eady have been investigating Sam before November 9, and therefore S&amp;C=
=E2=80=99s meeting with the U.S. attorney=E2=80=99s office that day =E2=80=
=9Cmay have done little damage=E2=80=9D to Sam and indeed, =E2=80=9Cmay hav=
e helped to prevent greater harm to the company.=E2=80=9D They questioned w=
hy Sam=E2=80=99s attorneys at Paul Weiss didn=E2=80=99t do more to warn him=
 about the repercussions of the Omnibus Corporate Authority document and ho=
w the appointment of Ray would change things for him dramatically. But, the=
y also note, there is =E2=80=9Cno evidence=E2=80=9D that Paul Weiss, or Sam=
, knew that S&amp;C had =E2=80=9Cgone to prosecutors=E2=80=9D before Sam re=
linquished control of FTX to Ray in the early morning hours of November 11.=
 But he did it all the
same.<br/><br/>Overall, Lipson and Skeel described Cleary=E2=80=99s report =
as a mixed bag. =E2=80=9CHe reports some important information that was not=
 previously known publicly, and he did so under difficult conditions,=E2=80=
=9D they explained. =E2=80=9CUnfortunately, he does not engage evidence tha=
t appears to be critical=E2=80=94in particular the timing of S&amp;C emails=
 reassuring Bankman-Fried of his role at FTX without disclosing that the fi=
rm had gone to prosecutors. He seems to rely heavily on the fact that Bankm=
an-Fried had his own counsel, which has never been in dispute. The importan=
t question is: What did those lawyers know about what S&amp;C did, and when=
 did they know it? If there is an answer to that question in the Examiner=
=E2=80=99s Report, we have yet to see it.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>The professors =
have a point. In any case, now that Cleary=E2=80=99s report has cleared S&a=
mp;C, we=E2=80=99ll likely have to wait until Sam=E2=80=99s appeal to see w=
hether there is anything more to his theory that Sullivan &amp; Cromwell th=
rew him under the
bus during its November 9 meeting. You can bet he=E2=80=99s thinking about =
it, and little else, during his diesel therapy.<br/></td>
